1.11 Part j
Create a function called evaluate.row(...) that takes one argument and returns “low” when the argument is less than 4, “mid” when the argument is between 4 and 7 (inclusive), and “high” when the arguement is 8 or larger. Then, use sapply(...) to apply it to column x1. Solution



Code
evaluate.row = function(x){
  if(x &lt; 4){
    return("low")
  }
  else if(x &lt;= 7){
    return("mid")
  }
  else if (x &gt;= 8){
    return("high")
  }
 }
sapply(df$x1, evaluate.row)


