4.3 Part c
Write a function that computes the log-likelihood for Altham’s Multiplicative Binomial Distribution, given data (x) and proposed parameter values \(p\) (prob) and \(\theta\) (theta).
Solution Here is the code for that function.



Code
loglikelihood = function(x, p, theta, n=11) {
  sum = 0
  for (i in 1:length(x))
    sum = sum + log(daltbinom(x = x[i], p = p, theta = theta, size = 11))
  return(sum)
}

1.3 Part F
Clean up the data entry. Replace the shorthand the researchers used with the neat sample type (Healthy Donor or THP-1), cell type (Monocytes or Macrophages), and treatment (12 Hours Post-Infection or Uninfected). Update dat.kitsberg.cleaned with the result.
Solution
In this code, I use the mutate() and case_when() functions like I did previously to change shorthand to the neat sample type described in the question.



Code
dat.kitsberg.cleaned = dat.kitsberg.cleaned |&gt;
  mutate( # section to change CellType into the shorthand
    CellType = case_when(
      CellType == "mac" ~ "Macrophage", 
      CellType == "mono" ~ "Monoctye",
      .default = CellType
    )
  ) |&gt; 
  mutate( #section to change Treatment into the shorthand
    Treatment = case_when(
      Treatment == "12hpi" ~ "12 Hours Post-Infection", 
      .default = Treatment
    )
  ) |&gt;
  mutate( #changing SampleType into the shorthand
    SampleType = case_when(
      SampleType == "primary" ~ "Healthy Donor", 
      SampleType == "THP1" ~ "THP-1",
      .default = SampleType
    )
  )



Hint: I would use the mutate(...) function. You will likely find if_else(...) or case_when(...) helpful.

1.4 Part G
In an R code block, combine your answers into one code block that completes the full cleaning process. Save the object as dat.kitsberg.cleaned.
Solution
In this code, I combine all my previous code and pipe it together. It produces the same result as the individual code.



Code
dat.kitsberg.cleaned = data.kitsberg |&gt;
  # the below code is the code i used earlier
  # it separates the column, and then filters the data
  # so only the desired columns are chosen
  separate(col = sample, into= c("SampleType", "CellType", "Treatment"), sep = '_' ) |&gt;
  filter(Treatment=="12hpi") |&gt; 
  select(SampleType, CellType, Treatment, 'viruses within nucleus') |&gt; 
  mutate(
    CellType = case_when(
      CellType == "MDM" ~ "mac", 
      .default = CellType
    )
  ) |&gt;
  filter(CellType =="mac" | CellType=="mono") |&gt; 
  mutate(
    CellType = case_when(
      CellType == "mac" ~ "Macrophage", 
      CellType == "mono" ~ "Monocyte",
      .default = CellType
    )
  ) |&gt;
  mutate(
    Treatment = case_when(
      Treatment == "12hpi" ~ "12 Hours Post-Infection", 
      .default = Treatment
    )
  ) |&gt;
  mutate(
    SampleType = case_when(
      SampleType == "primary" ~ "Healthy Donor", 
      SampleType == "THP1" ~ "THP-1",
      .default = SampleType
    )
  )


dat.kitsberg.cleaned &lt;- dat.kitsberg.cleaned |&gt;
  mutate(CellType2 = factor(CellType,
                            levels=c('Monocyte', 'Macrophage'))
  )



